<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-11T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7726: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-11T15:00:00+07:00">January 11,
                                1944—3 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 3:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>61. I called on Generalissimo this morning by appointment, accompanied by
                            Atcheson,<note n="28" xml:id="d613fn28">George Atcheson, Jr., Counselor
                            of Embassy.</note> delivered message and found occasion to make comments
                        suggested (25, January 5, 5 p.m.). Kung was present, acted as interpreter
                        and translated message to Chiang. While Kung made some deprecatory remarks
                        to Generalissimo in regard to the Treasury recommendations, they both
                        received the message affably <pb facs="0848" n="834" xml:id="pg_834"/> and
                        the Generalissimo thanked me for delivering it and indicated that after
                        study of it he would wish to make reply.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>